    <string name="description1">n the home screen, you can select one of the
        pre-existing profiles or create a new profile.</string>
    <string name="description2">A profile screen contains multiple
        buttons that each have their own function. You can also edit a profile
        by clicking on the “pencil” icon.</string>
    <string name="description3">When editing a profile, you can change its name,
        the order of the buttons and you can add and remove buttons. By typing the name of a program
        in the “Associated programs” text field, you can connect a profile to a program. When you
        have another profile open, and you open the associated program of another profile,
        that associated profile will open.</string>
    <string name="description4">You can change the name, picture/colour and description of
        any macro.</string>
    <string name="description5">You can edit the amount of repetitions and the delay between those
        repetitions for each action. You can also create a new action by pressing the plus
        button.</string>
    <string name="description6">After pressing the plus button, you have to choose an action type.
        After that you have to follow the instructions on the screen.</string>
    <string name="description7">In the settings you can change the language and colour of the app.
        And you can replay this tutorial.</string>
